.\" filetype.1 - manpage for filetype/editcmd
.\" Generated from filetype v1.1.0
.TH FILETYPE 1 "2026-03-10" "filetype 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
filetype \- determine file type and return editor-specific syntax name
.br
editcmd \- launch editor with correct syntax highlighting and line positioning
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B filetype
.RI [ options ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.IR filename " ..."
.br
.B editcmd
.RI [ options ]
.IR filename
.br
.B source filetype
&&
.B filetype
.IR filename
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B filetype
detects file types and returns syntax names suitable for editor syntax
highlighting.
It recognises 100+ file extensions, common special filenames
(Dockerfile, Makefile, .bashrc, etc.), shebang lines, and MIME types.
.PP
.B editcmd
is a symlink to
.B filetype
that triggers editor-launch mode via
.B $0
dispatch (busybox-style).
It opens the specified file in the user's editor with automatic syntax
highlighting and optional line positioning.
.PP
When
.B filetype
is
.B source\fRd as a library, it exports four functions and the variable
.B FILETYPE_VERSION
without entering any CLI mode.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS filetype options
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-editor " " \fIEDITOR\fR
Return syntax name for the specified editor.
Supported editors:
.BR joe ,
.BR nano ,
.BR vim ,
.BR emacs ,
.BR vscode ,
.BR helix ,
.BR micro ,
.BR zed .
Default: detected from
.B $EDITOR
environment variable, or
.B joe
if not set.
.TP
.B \-\-
End of options.
Allows filenames starting with
.BR \- .
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.
.SS editcmd options
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-editor " " \fIEDITOR\fR
Editor to use.
Same supported editors as above.
Default: detected from
.BR $EDITOR ,
or
.B vim
if not set.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-line\-no " " \fINUM\fR
Jump to line
.IR NUM .
.TP
.BI + NUM
Jump to line
.I NUM
(vim-style shorthand).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-print ", " \-\-dry\-run
Print the editor command without executing it.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.
.SH DETECTION ORDER
.B filetype
determines the file type using the following cascade:
.IP 1. 4
.B Special filename matching
\(em Dockerfile, Makefile, .bashrc, .env, .gitignore, Jenkinsfile,
Vagrantfile, CMakeLists.txt, etc.
.IP 2.
.B Extension matching
\(em 100+ extensions mapped to syntax names
(.sh \(-> sh, .py \(-> python, .js \(-> js, .cpp \(-> c, etc.)
.IP 3.
.B Directory detection
\(em returns
.BR directory .
.IP 4.
.B Non-existent file
\(em returns
.BR text .
.IP 5.
.B Shebang line inspection
\(em reads the first line for #! patterns
(#!/bin/bash \(-> sh, #!/usr/bin/env python3 \(-> python, etc.)
.IP 6.
.B MIME type analysis
\(em via
.BR file (1)
command.
.IP 7.
.B Binary file detection
\(em ELF, PE32, Mach-O, compiled, compressed, archive,
and application/* MIME types.
.IP 8.
.B Default fallback
\(em returns
.BR text .
.
.SH EDITOR MAPPING
The base syntax name returned by
.BR filetype ()
is mapped to editor-specific names by
.BR map_to_editor ().
.PP
.TS
allbox tab(|);
lb lb lb lb lb lb
l l l l l l.
Base|joe|nano|vim|emacs|vscode
sh|sh|sh|sh/bash|sh-mode|shellscript
python|python|python|python|python-mode|python
c|c|c|c|c-mode|c
c (C++)|c|c|cpp|c++-mode|cpp
js|js|javascript|javascript|javascript-mode|javascript
jsx|jsx|jsx|javascriptreact|js-jsx-mode|javascriptreact
md|md|markdown|markdown|markdown-mode|markdown
diff|diff|patch|diff|diff-mode|diff
makefile|makefile|makefile|make|makefile-mode|makefile
zsh|zsh|zsh|zsh|sh-mode|shellscript
.TE
.PP
.BR helix ", " micro ", and " zed
use syntax passthrough (tree-sitter auto-detection).
.
.SH LIBRARY USAGE
When sourced, the following functions are exported:
.TP
.BI filetype " filename"
Returns the base syntax name for
.IR filename .
.TP
.B detect_editor_from_env
Returns the editor type from
.BR $EDITOR
(default:
.BR joe ).
.TP
.BI map_to_editor " syntax" " [filename]"
Maps a base syntax name to an editor-specific name.
Uses
.B $EDITOR_TYPE
if set, otherwise calls
.BR detect_editor_from_env .
.TP
.BI build_editor_command " editor syntax filename" " [line_no]"
Generates a full editor launch command string.
Returns non-zero for binary files and directories.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source filetype
syntax=$(filetype "script.py")
echo "$syntax"                  # python
cmd=$(build_editor_command vim python script.py 42)
echo "$cmd"                     # vim +42 -c 'set filetype=python' script.py
.fi
.RE
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used to auto-detect the editor type.
.B filetype
defaults to
.B joe
when unset;
.B editcmd
defaults to
.BR vim .
.TP
.B EDITOR_TYPE
When set, overrides auto-detection in
.BR map_to_editor ().
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (missing file argument, binary file, directory for editcmd).
.TP
.B 22
Invalid argument (EINVAL: bad option, invalid editor name).
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS filetype
.nf
filetype script.sh                  # sh
filetype -e nano app.js             # javascript
filetype -e vim README.md           # markdown
filetype -e emacs program.py        # python-mode
filetype -e vscode file.sh          # shellscript
filetype -e vim file1.sh file2.js   # file1.sh: bash
                                    # file2.js: javascript
filetype /bin/ls                    # binary
filetype /tmp                       # directory
filetype -- -oddname.py             # python
.fi
.SS editcmd
.nf
editcmd script.py                   # Open with auto-detected syntax
editcmd -l 42 script.py             # Jump to line 42
editcmd +42 script.py               # Vim-style: jump to line 42
editcmd -e nano script.py           # Use nano
editcmd --dry-run script.py         # Print command only
editcmd +100 -e vim test.c          # Multiple options
.fi
.SS Shell integration
.nf
# Quick edit function
edit() {
  local syntax
  syntax=$(filetype "$1")
  joe -syntax "$syntax" "$1"
}

# Jump to linter error
error_line=$(pylint script.py | grep -oP 'line \eK\ed+' | head -1)
editcmd -l "$error_line" script.py
.fi
.
.SH FILES
